        <comment>
  <id>102237572</id>
  <body><![CDATA[Yeah, I knew I was seeking out a good friend when I requested your friendship. Of course, I am among the besotted where this novel is concerned. I highly recommend <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/114408.Mockingbird_A_Portrait_of_Harper_Lee" title="Mockingbird A Portrait of Harper Lee by Charles J. Shields" rel="nofollow">Mockingbird: A Portrait of Harper Lee</a> by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/9460.Charles_J__Shields" title="Charles J. Shields" rel="nofollow">Charles J. Shields</a>, an unauthorized biography. Ms. Lee dared friends to buy the book considering it an invasion of her privacy. However, this is a very respectful portrait of the reclusive author. There is also a new release I'll be checking out. <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18693728.The_Mockingbird_Next_Door_Life_with_Harper_Lee" title="The Mockingbird Next Door Life with Harper Lee by Marja Mills" rel="nofollow">The Mockingbird Next Door: Life with Harper Lee</a> by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7353452.Marja_Mills" title="Marja Mills" rel="nofollow">Marja Mills</a>.<br /><br />Harper Lee based Atticus Finch on her father, Amasa Lee, a lawyer in small town Monroeville, Al. Harper Lee attended Huntington College in Montgomery, Al, the University of Alabama, and the University of Alabama School of Law. She graduated from none of them. Yet she received the necessary education from her father, her community, and her unerring sense of fairness, right and wrong.<br /><br />I've had occasion to visit the iconic courthouse portrayed in the movie. The curator allowed me to go downstairs and examine the records of the courts. Those records presented cases a hundred years ago that could easily be in any courtroom today.<br /><br />In each their own way the book and movie are among my favorites. The soundtrack makes excellent background music for reading the novel.<br /><br />To Lefty from Pancho (See All the Federales Say, Willie Nelson)]]></body>
  
